CODE BOLD START--><b> Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Bard<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  -Brief history-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Laurelai was the single child of two half elves who lived in the East Commonlands.  Her mother was a bard, and her father a craftsman.  When she was 5, her mother sent her to Freeport to pick up some supplies for her father, and she dawdled in town looking at people and wares.  When she returned home, her family cottage had been burned to the ground by the Deathfist orcs and her mother and father killed.  She was found and adopted by a ranger who taught her the ways of Tunare.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>When she was 13 years old, her adopted family traveled to Kelethin.  During the boat trip, Laurelai became very despondant- she had been a quiet and sad child after the death of her parents.  She decided that she would end it on this boat trip, and leapt off the boat intending to drown.  She swam away from the boat, and swam down under the water as far as she could.  As she began to feel she was going to black out, Prexus surrounded her with a bubble of air and spoke to her.  She had been spared death and converted to worship of Prexus.  She became his bard and by his direction began to look for joy in her life to balance out the sorrow.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Laurelai is an older mature self-confident hedonist to the hilt.  She has a passion for fine food, fine drink, and great music.  She also has a great drive to learn.  That perhaps has been a driving force behind her neutrality- she is a master of all civilized tongues, and knows many of the languages from such beings as fairies and the Froglocks.  She desires to learn whatever she can to add to her great collection of lore.  She is very lawful by nature, but that provides her world with order, not constraint.  She enjoys making things for friends, helping strangers, and trying to make people's lives more joyful.  She laughs at anything, anyone including herself.  She is a sceptic though, and she needs to have things shoved in her face before she will believe it.<br><br>One word or phrase that sums Laurelai up- <br>Joy <p>Laurelai Lifelyric 55 bard Innoruuk server <br> Master chef- 147<br> Master brewer- 168<br>Master fisherman- 183<br> Master potter- 125<br>Master guzzler- 200<br> Almost there smith- 87<br>Sucky Tailor- 35 (I'll put more holes in your pants than I fix! :/)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulaurelai01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laurelai01</A> at: 1/5/02 7:13:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=laurelai>Laurelai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 6:09:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> (just because I am on a roll, I'll reply to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alathu Dara`Thex</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Race:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> High Elf<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Age:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 130 years old<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alignment:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Lawful Good<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Home city:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Felwithe<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Cleric<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> -Brief history-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Alathu is the oldest of two girls in her family.  Her younger sister has just discovered that she has the ability to use her power in the manner of wizards.  Alathu is very fond of her younger sister, and writes to her often.  Her parents are both High elven Paladins, and were proud to find that their eldest had the ability to heal.  They sent her to study under the clerics of Felwithe where she excelled.  She is related to royalty by a very convoluted chain of relatives, but that is insignificant to her.  She is related to royalty and that is what she acknowledges.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Alathu had no choice in the matter of worship.  She was brought up a Tunarean by her religiously adherant family.  She abides by the tenet of her religion to the letter, and has little tolerance for those who are less pious.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Personality</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>As intellegent as she is, Alathu does not realize that she lacks empathy.  When she heals, she feels that the person in need of healing has failed to protect themselves, or has acted foolishly.  She does what she does well, but is driven not by a need to serve, instead she is motivated by pride.  She brooks no failure on her part because it would reflect badly on her family.  She observes the world through cool eyes, not showing outward passion for anything save her family.  It is almost as if she performs her work grudgingly.<br><br>One word or phrase that sums Alathu up-<br>Pride<br><br> <p><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/thelizards/laur2.jpg><br>Laurelai Lifelyric<br>Mana Battery Extraordinaire</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uvaeluudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaeluudar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/slytlidisturbed/images/thev.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 6:19:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://publish.hometown.aol.com/slytlidisturbed/images/thev.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Vaeluudar Asha'man</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Race</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Dark Elf<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Age</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Roughly 320 years, though he's been quoted as being around during events that happened nearly five hundred his time.<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alignment</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Chaotic Good<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Home city</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Neriak, though is seeking a Fiefdom within Luclin.<br>-Brief history-<br><br>Family:<br>Mother a High Priestess of Innoruuk, while father was a Smith in the Neriak Forges. Nothing eventful from the family, save for his older brother Millienium and he being forced through seperate schools of magicks as a family tradition.<br><br>Religion:<br>Much to the dismay and disapproval of his entire family, his mother most of all, he chooses no sides in the eternal wars of the Gods. He realized at a young age that what he dabbled in could quite possibly allow him to destroy any of them.. so why worship that which he might become?<br><br>Personality:<br>He's a man of violence, without actually having to get himself dirty. Chaotic, with the slightest hint of madness, he loves to bring destruction to those about him who, for whatever reason, brought it upon themselves. He lives at the constant edge of every spectrum.. either with fierce hatred, or fierce loyalty to those who have actually befriended him. There is no middle ground for Vaeluudar.<br><br>Over the last few years, though, something has crept into his soul. Something a little more twisted that he had used to be. Maybe it's the realization of the powers he wields.. or maybe it's the realization that he has yet to hold as much power as he <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> should</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be wielding. Whatever it is.. he's become a lot more ruthless with his killing, laying waste to those who fall within his displeasure like many fields of corn to a farmer's scythe.<br><br><br>One word or phrase that sums Vaeluudar up- <br>Madness<br><br> <p><br><br><p><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/slytlidisturbed/images/vaeluudar.jpg"></p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60323">Vaeluudar's Profile</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/binnoruukserver.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=laurelai>Laurelai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 7:30:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> Oh ok- just one more..... since you insist! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Whilhamena Blackbrew</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Age:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 23<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Race:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Barbarian<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Alignment:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Chaotic neutral<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Home city:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Halas<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Rogue<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> -Brief History-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Whil is very tight-lipped about her family.  It isn't even known if her parents are alive any longer.  If questioned, she will use humor and change the subject (a talent she has become very skilled at).  She was on her own at least at the age of 14 and fell in with what could be termed the &quot;wrong crowd&quot;.  These people became her family.  Her street friends are loose-knit, but it is as close as she has to anything resembling family.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>While she follows Bristlebane, she only does so half-heartedly.  She follows the beliefs of the rogue's god, but she doesn't feel any sense of duty or obligation to put herself out in the name of religion.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Whil is outwardly friendly.  She has decided that sugar catches more flies than vinegar, but she will never truely open up to anyone who is not in her kin-group from her adolescent age.  One thing about Whil is she is very vain.  She has refused to take the woad markings that are part of Halas culture.  Green eyed with a sprinkling of freckles across her nose, she feels that her face is an asset, and to cover it would reduce the effectiveness of one of her &quot;tools&quot;.  She shuns hard work, but does have an extensive knowlege of the art of poison-craft.  She has been known to make great trips out of her way to gather ingredients for her brews.... and she has no compunction what so ever against slipping her hand into that fat purse at the cleric's waist.  A gal's gotta eat ya know!<br><br>One word or phrase that sums Whilhamena up-<br>Self-centered <p><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/thelizards/laur2.jpg><br>Laurelai Lifelyric<br>Mana Battery Extraordinaire</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 10:18:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xtimports.com/data/graphics/Aldrinshroom1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> Hm. <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Aldrin of the Nexus</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (nee Aldrin Moonwalker)<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Age:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> unknown, suspected to be at least 400.<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Race:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> gnome<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Alignment:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Chaotic good<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Home City:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Highpass Hold (he has an apt there)<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Wizard<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   -Brief History-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Family:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>No one knows where Aldrin came from. For some, he's always been, for others, he's just appeared at the least opportune time. Stories can be found in Ak Anon claiming that his father was a mage and his mother an enchantress, but who they were and whatever happened to them remains a mystery. Aldrin has a very loose association of friends spanning all of Norrath and its moons which he might consider family, even though some might be considered mortal enemies to each other. Everywhere he goes he finds someone who knows him with affection, probably because he travels widely and likes everyone until they prove themselves unlikable.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Aldrin's chosen deity is Solusek Ro, purely for business purposes. His preferred diety might be Bristlebane, for he loves laughter and music, and is almost irresistably attracted to rogues and bards.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Emotionally, Aldrin is six and three-quarter years old, in spite of his possible age. No one knows why he developed his characteristic lisp, but it does cause him exceptional embarassment and he can be brought to tears by those cruel enough to make fun of him for it. <br>Aldrin loves life, and is fascinated by the people he encounters. He doesn't really view anyone as bad, until they try to hurt him or someone he likes. He is indescriminate in this; he's been known to challenge Al Kabor himself over insults directed at a recently acquired friend.<br>Ultimately courageous, Aldrin too often volunteers to take the brunt of damage in  a battle to spare his companions the pain and risk of death that such activities often entail. When a battle goes badly, and evacuation is not an option, he's been known to cast area effect spells or otherwise aggrevate his opponents in an attempt to buy time for his companions to escape or regroup and heal. Rarely does this work. <br>Aldrin's secret dream is to someday become a barbarian, preferably a warrior. He is totally fascinated by the harsh yet compassionate lifestyle forced upon them by their native climate. The sheer size of barbarians might have something to do with it as well. <br>If he can be located nowhere else, he often can be found in Halas, in the dog pens petting and playing with the Barbarian's True Companions. The dogs, with their instinctive recognition of good and evil, always welcome him into their company, and have even been known to growl menacingly at their master if s/he should wander too close while Aldrin is present.<br><br>One word to describe Aldrin:<br><br>Aldrin.<br><br>(addendum: anyone wishing to learn the nature of Aldrin should read Rudyard Kipling's &quot;Wee Willie Winkie&quot;)<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.bibliomania.com/0/5/frameset.html">www.bibliomania.com/0/5/frameset.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br> <p>Aldrin of the Nexus<BR><a href="http://www.xtimports.com/index.html"><img src="http://www.xtimports.com/data/Everquest/pics/Aldrinsig2.jpg" alt="Extra Terrestrial Imports " align="left" border="0" hspace="0" width="240" height="263"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/5/02 1:05:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 11:13:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xtimports.com/data/graphics/Aldrinshroom1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Rhysling</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Age:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 30-ish<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Race:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Human<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Alignment</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Chaotic neutral<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Home City</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Kelethin<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Class:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Bard<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  -Brief History-</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>When Rhysling was but a babe, his family migrated from Qeynos to Highpass. Beset by unknown forces, the caravan was utterly destroyed, save himself and one other child. <br>By the time he was found by a group of travelling wood elf rangers and druids, the other child had disappeared, and he was nearly dead of exposure. As one ranger was about to dispatch the ugly creature to put him out of his misery, the druid became unnerved by the unwavering gaze from the waif, and halted the execution. After a brief discussion it was decided to bring the child to Kelethin; there he would be judged and his fate decided by Tunare.<br>Rhysling was fortunately spared, and raised atop Kelethin by the entire community. This was not generosity of spirit; it was the only way to resolve the elven sense of responsibility without burdening any family with the stain of human association.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Religion:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Raised as he was, Rhysling views everything with irreverence. No belief, however dearly held, is above analysis and ridicule. He leans toward Bristlebane as his deity of choice, since Bristlebane most closely mirrors his own world view.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Personality:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Rhysling is a loner. It's not a distrust or distaste for others, but simple self-reliance born of his elven upbringing. He needs no one else, and is therefore as comfortable alone as in company. His songs he sings for his own entertainment; if they also move others, he's appreciative, but indifferent. He left Kelethin upon achieving manhood and joining the Bardic guild, seeking to find knowledge of the events surrounding his family's death. Though he lost one eye in a boyhood accident (a prank gone awry,) the other retains the keen intensity that so unnerved the druid who was his benefactor.<br>Having traveled the worlds, he's found that all Great Causes are often greater in the mind than in reality. As a result, Rhysling developed a mercenary attitude, with his loyalty belonging to his companions in battle, rather than to the cause for which he is paid to fight.<br><br>One word to describe Rhysling:<br>individual<br><br> <p>Aldrin of the Nexus<BR><a href="http://www.xtimports.com/index.html"><img src="http://www.xtimports.com/data/Everquest/pics/Aldrinsig2.jpg" alt="Extra Terrestrial Imports " align="left" border="0" hspace="0" width="240" height="263"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/6/02 5:43:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uunilove.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unilove</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/5/02 12:08:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> Nice thread!  More!!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f