out the entire caravan - or so they thought. During the battle Dorim was seperated from his family and friends in the Kithicor Woods. A ranger found him the next morning and aided him in returning to Kaladim. <br><br>His entire family slain, Dorim returned home Broken hearted. Upon entering the Temple of Brell in Kaladim he felt his spirits lifted and knew this was the destiny for him. Following his heart he changed his name from Stoneshield to Soulshield. He has sought to follow the spiritual path instead of seeking revenge upon the dark elves.<br><br>Only recently was he reunited with his long lost (and thought dead) brother, Grimfold Stoneshield.<br><br>Religion:<br>As said before - Dorim is a worshipper of Brell. His honesty and wisdom has allowed him to move up quickly within the Church of Brell.<br><br>Personality:<br>Dorim is true to his word. He does not lie and goes out of his way to help others in need. As kindly as he is to those who know him, he may seem gruff and stubborn to those who just meet him. He believes in the power of Brell with all of his being and seeks to right wrongs wherever he may find them.<br><br>Dorim cares deeply for his long lost brother (Grimfold) but feels that the events of the past have left a stain on his brothers heart that cannot be washed away easily. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29713"><img src="http://www.somuchtuttle.com/pics/eq/soulshieldbanner.jpg" border=0></center></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uctuttle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ctuttle</A> at: 1/6/02 6:10:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umegunna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Megunna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/6/02 5:10:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?