ld not survive if he were brought into Neriak itself Grimfold made a daring escape and found himself alone and lost in the lands of man known as The Commons.<br><br>Here he spent many years among humans in the city of Freeport - only when he had gained skill in battle and strength to face his broken heart did he return to Kaladim. <br><br>Religion:<br>Grimfold is a worshipper of Brell.<br><br>Personality:<br>Due to the loss of his family, Grimfold has a deep loathing for dark elves. For several years he belonged to a group of like minded individuals known as The Bloodguard - others who had been effected by the workings of Neriak and Innoruuk as he had. <br><br>Many dark elves had their blood spilt in battle with The Bloodguard and many more lost their lives to Grimfolds axe. However, each killing did not fix the pain in his heart. It only seemed to deepen the sadness. He has since come to terms that not all dark elves, as not all dwarves, are the same.<br><br>He is still not comfortable among them or in their presence but he tolerates them.<br><br>Grimfold is quick to anger, gruff, stubborn, and just about everything you would expect from a dwarf. Still - if you look closely - you can see a sadness in his eyes. And if you look closer still... you can see a shadow on his heart.<br> <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29713"><img src="http://www.somuchtuttle.com/pics/eq/soulshieldbanner.jpg" border=0></center></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utoham.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toham</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/6/02 6:43:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezb