 said that one does not choose their God, but the God chooses you, and Rallos Zek chose Jolene.  Rallos Zek would invade from the dream world, causing Jolene much grief.  How dare a God disturb her slumber!  Sheesh!  But Jolene could not deny she was meant to follow him, as Rallos Zek was obviously impressed enough to come to her in a state more associated with peace.  The only thing that didn't bode well with her was His demands.  Survival of the strong, genocide of the weak.  Being the child of loving parents, she found it hard to swallow those laws.  So, she made her own laws.  She would choose selective genocide as opposed to all and out elimination.  She was not so weak, though, should the opportunity arise where she was required to defend her life.  Was not her fault that some poor slob managed to walk into the point of her sword.  And to complicate matters more, Rallos Zek had decreed that she, a human, would be soulbound to an Ogre.  Why it was done this way, no one knows, nor does Jolene question it.  While she does revel in defying Rallos Zek on occasion, she does have a very healthy respect for his diciplines.  And when she met her destined mate, Gugtukarjunior III, Gug for short, she knew her life was in for a wild ride.<br><br>Personality<br>Jolene lives on the wild side of life.  Even though she had the loving influence of her parents, and a thriving relationship with them, which isn't what most adult children can say about their parents, she considers herself a loner, an outcast, partly because of Gug.  While she loves him more than her own life, and will die for him,  but because he is an Ogre, they are not welcome in most cities.  Jolene counts among her friends the social misfits of society:  Rogues, Necromancers, Shadow Knights, Dark Elves, Trolls, Ogres, and Iksar.<br><br>Summary of Jolene<br>Independant<br><br><br>/ooc  Sorry for age changes.  Jolene has had a few birthdays between this and previously written stories as stated below.<br> <p>Lenore BravehardAmbassador to EoNDevoted wife and faithful companion of Choco Bravehard"Have you hugged a Dragon today?"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulenoreb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenoreb</A> at: 1/7/02 10:57:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulenoreb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenoreb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/7/02 12:03:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=878.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character profiles (not Magelo)</span><hr size=1> Elishia Gerstuhl<br>Race  Erudite<br>Age  40<br>Alignment  Lawful Good<br>Home city  Erudin<br>Occupation  Paladin<br><br>Family life<br>Often left alone as a young child, Elishia grew up not knowing what was beyond the walls of her home.  At the age of eight, she followed her parents on one of their daily excursions without their knowledge.   Elishia was terrified of the sights and sounds of the forest around her home.  Toxxulia was a dense forest, frequently filled with a foul smelling ever present green haze.  The source of this haze remains unknown, which suits the Erudites just nicely, since the choking gas forces possible pilgrims to leave instead of settle on Odus.  As Elishia entered a secret cave, the sounds of screams, screams of those in pain, and dying.  It was made painfully aware to her she stumbled upon a city controlled by the Heretics she heard some residents in Erudin talk about, as she watched in horror as her parents walked by with skeletal slaves behind them.  Upon her discovery, she fled for her life, back to the safety of Erudin, and collapsed on the steps of the Temple of Quellious.<br><br>Religion<br>Quellious<br>Since she embraced no God, the Clerics and Paladins schooled her.  She had a natural gift of life, as Quellious had seen it and had led her to them, just as Quellious said would happen.  Elishia seemed to be under the personal protection of the Tranquil One.  Elishia trained and studied hard, and was embraced as a Holy Crusader for Quellious.  But, eventually, Elishia was forced to flee her only home, her Sanctuary, since it was not safe as long as her parents were alive.  So, under the darkness of night, at the tender age of seventeen, she sailed eastward, toward Qeynos.  And there, her life would change yet again.<br><br>Personality<br>Elishia is a gentle soul, prefering conversation over conflict.  However, she is not so passive to let a deadly threat against her life go unanswered.  She has but one mission in life, and that is to eliminate the evil of her parents, no matter the cost.  And she is not alone in her quest.  When she arrived in Qeynos,  she met a man schooled in the healing magics.  Heili was a Cleric, serving under Karana.  The two formed a bond, in which the shy Elishia thrived on his love and constant attention.  In turn, her quiet manner soothed his tortured soul, as he was an orphan since bandits murdered his parents.  Only him and his older brother, Choco, survived that attack.  <br><br>Summary of Elishia<br>Shy, yet strong<br><br><br><br>/ooc  sorry for changing the age of Elishia.  Trying to have this correspond with previous stories so not to have events and ages clash.  However, in previous stories, Elishia was much younger.<br> <p>Lenore BravehardAmbassador to EoNDevoted wife and faithful companion of Choco Bravehard"Have you hugged a Dragon today?"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulenoreb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenoreb</A> at: 1/7/02 10:53:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=ti