ter.  There, she met a man, a brother of the arts, and a fellow Erudian.  Her future husband.  His name was Madnbad.  The two formed a bond unique to the human race, shunned by other races, primarliy the Teir'Dal, as Love was weak, and for the weak, and Hatred was the only way to live, as Innoruuk was supreme.<br><br>Personality<br>Zianya is often a uncertain individual, hiding behind the mask of independence, often coming across to people as haughty and superior because of her race.  The truth is, she is very uncertain of her abilities, and became uncertain about her quest.  As time went on, she discovered hidden away memories and conflicting stories, as she finally met up with her sister, Elishia.  And that meeting was not a cry for her sister's blood, but a desire to know the truth.  And that stark truth was that both girls were but pawns to a pair of people too cowardly to do their own duties befitting their station in life.  And that day, Zianya grew up quickly.  She formed a strong bond with her sister, and together, were able to vanquish the lies and treachery of their parents.  While the victory was sweet for Zianya, it was bitter for her gentle sister.  In an effort to help her sister cope, in a way uncommon to a child of darkness, she told Elishia to look at it as a cleansing, sanctioned in the name of Quellious.  It worked.<br><br>Summary of Zianya<br>Strong, yet quietly supportive of common goals<br><br><br>/ooc Again sorry to change the age of Zianya.  Same reasons as stated above.  Zianya has aged a few years since &quot;Bloodlines&quot; was written. <p>Lenore BravehardAmbassador to EoNDevoted wife and faithful companion of Choco Bravehard"Have you hugged a Dragon today?"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulenoreb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenoreb</A> at: 1/7/02 10:55:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ujustallys